   JSC's DIGITAL IMAGERY COLLECTION NASA's Johnson Space Center is proud
   to provide this collection of all cataloged Shuttle mission
   Earth-looking imagery from the first shuttle mission, STS-1, through
   STS-76, a total of nearly 250,000 images. This collection also includes
   press release images from the manned space program, from Mercury to the
   STS-81 Shuttle mission. This collection represents over 10,000 images.
   These images can be accessed via the World Wide Web (WWW) in JPEG
   format (average size 40k each), along with the text files that describe
   them, at the following web address: http://images.jsc.nasa.gov/
   Additional press release images are available on NASA's Human
   Spaceflight Web site, at this address:
   http://spaceflight.nasa.gov/gallery/images/shuttle/index.html More
   detailed catalog data for Shuttle mission Earth-looking imagery,
   catalog data for missions after STS-76, and additional imagery are
   available from JSC's Office of Earth Sciences at this address:
   http://eol.jsc.nasa.gov/sseop/ Further information regarding these
   images: JSC Office of Public Affairs External Affairs Branch Mail Code
   AP4 2101 NASA Road 1 Houston, TX 77058 Fax: (281) 483-2000
